liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Well, that was an interesting half. Both sides showed some moments of real danger, but neither have been able to finish off anything they've created. There's been a lot of defensive scrambling, with the Matildas arguably doing more of that than France, but Australia have probably had the more convincing opportunities in the box. A finely-balanced game so far. What do you think, team? Should Tony Gustavsson change something at half-time, or stick with what he's got so far? Who could shake this game up?
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Thoughts?
